The paper discusses a technique for finding linear representations of non-negative data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper also provides MATLAB code for the technique, indicating a focus on practical applications. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the notion of sparseness, which is a common topic in signal processing and compressed sensing, suggesting possible relevance to cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
